	     <tr><td id="headerrow" colspan="2" class="mform" valign="top"><a id="sj" href="">RE: Bad Groups</a> <a id="fs8" href="#post"><img src="/shared/reply_to_thread_ico.gif" border="0" alt="Reply..." width="17" height="11" /></a>
	     <br clear="all" /><small>Posted @ Thu, Jul 25th 3:29 PM 2002</small></td></tr>
	     <tr><td valign="top" id="fs8" class="mform"><span id="notbold">By:</span> <a href="/db/poster.html?user=175669"><span id=" ">Stoutoak</span></a><br /><span id="notbold">52 posts<br /><span id="notbold">Score</span>: Decent [3.00]</td><td valign=top class="mform" width="100%"><p>&nbsp;&nbsp;Lol you are calling other people greedy, when what you are saying is that you want things handed to you simply because you are the only class that can use it.  Everyone in the party cooperated and worked hard at the group... clerics healed, melees fought, casters mezzed, blasted, rooted, etc etc.  Why shouldn't they all be able to share equally in the loot that drops??  The ranger had just as much a chance to win the roll as anyone else, but they didn't, so stop whining and keep camping it, maybe you'll win the next one.  I have been screwed so many times, not being allowed to roll on supposed melee items (I am a cleric, btw) that I am sick of this NBG crap.  I would say without hesitation that some of the most frequently camped areas (talking pick-up groups) of the game drop 90% melee-oriented stuff, i.e. all areas of velks, most of sebilis, Howling stones.... 90% of the crap is melee.  That means, a cleric like myself, following YOUR rules, has to follow behind the melees and watch as they all get upgraded, while I just spend lots of cash on dots.  NBG has never worked in my favor, so I refuse to apply it to the poor,poor melees... who more often than not are secondary characters and twinks.<br/>  If you want things to work as NBG (need before greed), join a guild, thats the way mine works.  If you don't like guilds, get a group of five friends that always are on at the same time, and agree to go camp whatever piece of equipment you expect them to just hand over to you.  But if you are in a pick-up group, don't expect 5 strangers to just friggin give you upgrades.  Their time, abilities, and characters are worth just as much as yours, and they are entitled to roll on items equally, regardless of who can best use.  If they decide to play by NBG, thats great!!! But if you EXPECT them to, then you are the selfish one, my friend.</p>&nbsp;<br /></td></tr>
